		<div class="comment-body"><p>Yep part of my problem with every buying a BGE is how many more affordable versions are out there.  I imagine like many things you often get what you pay for but I have my doubts about that here.</p>
<p>The BGE works because of how think and insulated it is, that isn&#8217;t magic or a secret.  </p>
<p>I mean I can explain why to buy a weber over a cheap gas grill, I can show you parts that will fail in one and not the other, I can show the design of the drip pan, the gauge of the steel etc.</p>
<p>I have looked at some grills that are like the BGE and I can&#8217;t see much difference.  Most are hundreds of dollars less, not chump change.</p>
</div>

