				September 23, 2013 at 7:05 pm</a>
					|
													</span><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>Here&#8217;s a tip. Take a charcoal chimney and get it fully red hot blazing. Get it so the big open end looks like a jet engine. Throw some sort of grill/grate over the big open end. This is the best way to sear fish like swordfish, tuna, scallops, striper, etc.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s a little dangerous. Don&#8217;t leave unattended around dogs, kids or dummies.</p>
</div>

