		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>Well it is what I do, it kills two birds with one stone.  Knocks all the crud off and coats the iron at the same time.  I generally knock it off with a brush that isn&#8217;t oiled but it has oil from the last time.  Once cleaned I dump some oil on the brush and brush it more.  I do it till you can tell all the iron has some oil on it.</p>
</div>

